North- east of the Seine and the Marne, in the plains of Picardy, Artois, and champagne, on the mist-ladon flats of the Scheldt and the lower Rhine and in the vast forest of the Ardennes, dwelt the Belgae, who may have partially mixed and were continually at war with their German neighbours.
